.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH webp-mux 1  "mux " 
.SH NAME
mux \- Edit an animated WebP without re\-encoding frames (webpmux\-parity muxing)
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBmux\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Edit an animated WebP without re\-encoding frames (webpmux\-parity muxing).
.PP
Extract a frame, edit the loop count / background, or insert / remove / replace frames — every untouched frame\*(Aqs encoded bytes pass through byte\-for\-byte, and the ICC/Exif/XMP metadata is preserved.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
mux\-get\-frame(1)
Extract one frame as a standalone still WebP (bytes copied verbatim)
.TP
mux\-set(1)
Rewrite the loop count and/or background color
.TP
mux\-remove(1)
Remove one frame, rebuilding the frame list
.TP
mux\-insert(1)
Insert a still WebP as a new frame (its image bytes copied verbatim)
.TP
mux\-replace(1)
Replace one frame\*(Aqs image with a still WebP, keeping its placement/timing
.TP
mux\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
